1	National Coalition for Homeless Veterans	About 11% of the adult homeless population are veterans. Roughly 45% of all homeless veterans are African American or Hispanic, despite only accounting for 10.4% and 3.4% of the U.S. veteran population, respectively. ... Two-thirds served our country for at least three years, and one-third were stationed in a war zone.	http://nchv.org/index.php/news/media/background_and_statistics/
2	Homeless Veterans	Feb 21, 2012 ... Conservatively, one out of every three homeless men who is sleeping in a doorway, alley or box in our cities and rural communities has put on a uniform and served this country. Approximately 40% of homeless men are veterans, although veterans comprise only 34% of the general adult male population.	http://www.nationalhomeless.org/factsheets/veterans.html
